		Kevin Lee")) (item nil (title nil "Review: UpDesk PowerUp is a height-adjustable desk with more ups than downs") (description nil "
<article><section class=\"page\"><p>
Scientists say that prolonged sitting is bad for your health. So I try not to. Instead of sitting down at my desk each day for work, I stand at it. And, in fact, I walk. As I’ve <a href=\"http://www.macworld.com/article/1156988/treadmilldesk.html\">written</a><a href=\"http://www.techhive.com/article/2027963/review-lifespans-bluetooth-enabled-treadmill-desk-is-flawed-but-functional.html\">previously</a>, I walk while I work, at 2.5 miles per hour. I’m walking right now as I write these words.
</p><p>
Though my first standing desk was really a normal desk with cardboard boxes stacked atop it, I now use legitimate standing-height desks instead. But while I tread all day long, many standing desk users prefer to take occasional seated breaks. That’s where height-adjustable desks come in. I recently spent a couple months experimenting with a <a href=\"https://myupdesk.com/updesk/mahogany-small\">Mahogany UpDesk</a>, from a company also called UpDesk.
</p><figure class=\" original\"><img src=\"http://images.techhive.com/images/article/2013/05/mahogany-medium-1-100039680-orig.jpg\" height=\"388\" width=\"580\" alt=\" \"/><figcaption/></figure><p>
UpDesk sells a variety of adjustable desks, both mechanical (CrankUps) and electric (PowerUps). The Mahogany desk I reviewed was an electric one, the medium model: 60 inches wide by 30 inches deep. It can go as low as 26.5 inches tall, and as high as 42.5 inches tall.
</p><p>
That peak height, 42.5 inches, is a smidgen low for my needs. I’m 6’2”, standing atop a treadmill that adds several more inches. If you purchase the optional <a href=\"https://myupdesk.com/store/product/wheel-set-DKWS\">$59 wheel set</a> for the desk, that adds another three inches of height to the setup.
</p><p class=\"jumpTag\"><a href=\"/article/2040346/review-updesk-powerup-is-a-height-adjustable-desk-with-more-ups-than-downs.html#jump\">To read this article in full or to leave a comment, please click here</a></p></section></article>") (link nil "http://www.techhive.com/article/2040346/review-updesk-powerup-is-a-height-adjustable-desk-with-more-ups-than-downs.html#tk.rss_all") (media:thumbnail ((url . "http://zapt1.staticworld.net/images/article/2013/05/mahogany-medium-4-100039682-small.jpg"))) (media:content ((url . "http://zapt1.staticworld.net/images/article/2013/05/mahogany-medium-4-100039682-small.jpg"))) (pubDate nil "Tue, 04 Jun 2013 09:00:00 -0700") (author nil "
