Intel expects tablets containing its upcoming Atom processor, <a href=\"http://www.pcworld.com/article/2037549/intel-releases-key-details-of-its-atom-redesign.html\">code-named Bay Trail</a>, will cost under $200, a company executive said Wednesday.
</p><p>
