</p><p>
This is a new low price for tablets with Intel processors. Intel has revised its projected tablet price several times, with the most recent being for tablets between $200 and $399. Now the pressure is on device makers to offer Intel-based tablets under $199.
</p><p>
Tablets with Bay Trail will run Windows 8.1 and Android, Eul said. The inexpensive tablets will most likely have screens from 7 to 10 inches in size.
